Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 24
Edition:
Quote: cutty grass: several grasses having the capacity to cut one's skin have earned this name, but at least one of them has an appreciable usefulness. This is Carex ternaria, which grows in swampy ground. Where it can be sighted, there the ground can be trusted to bear a horse or a cattle beast.
